OL,7,F10% of female survey respondents
OL,8,Freported experiencing sexual
OL,9,Fharassment, with the report suggesting
OL,10,Fsexual assault or harassment continues
OL,11,Fto go largely underreported.
OL,13,FWhile the report into North Wales Fire
OL,14,FService acknowledged some improvements
OL,15,Fin culture, bullying and harassment
OL,16,Fcontinued to be "widespread" in the
OL,17,Fservice, with over two-fifths (42%) of
OL,18,Fsurvey respondents reporting personal
OL,19,Fexperiences since June 2021, and
OL,20,Fnearly half (49%) had witnessed such
OL,21,Fbehaviours.
